reviewText: Very low quality.  Total waste of money.  I threw it in the garbage
purchased this because it was dated 2016 and had a colorized  picture icon. I was surised it was an old black and white movie from the 40 or 50's. very misleading

This movie was released in 1944 and is in Black & White and of poor quality. I would say classic deception is a foot here. A Nazi spy passes himself off as an optometrist in San Francisco's waterfront district. Someone robs him of his codebook, and he must get it back. It stars John Carradine.
A pure, classic old film well worth a watch. They don't make em like this no more!

It says it is 2016 but that is only when it was added to Amazon.  It is a very old fiilm (B&W)
and not very interesting.
This is a black and white movie.  A classic?  Idk.
